    <description>There&#39;s a pretty snazzy looking roll20 challenger that launched on kickstarter today that has got me pretty psyched called [ROLE](https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/role/role-a-new-kind-of-platform-for-the-rpg-community): https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/role/role-a-new-kind-of-platform-for-the-rpg-community

If that drag-an-drop customizable character sheet works it&#39;s already a game-changer for me as a small publisher because getting a nice automated character sheet on a platform like roll20 is a popular ask these days but it&#39;s actually pretty expensive if you can&#39;t do it yourself (like me).

Love the focus on diversity, safety tools, more robust player matching options, as well as the other standard stuff you&#39;d need for running online.

